race.comment: SATTVA (14) was close up in a stronger maiden at Sandown Hillside first up, in the market there and only beaten 1.4 lengths into fifth. Tricky draw here but she'll be fitter and gets D Lane aboard who can offset that with a positive ride. CARRIEDO (6) resumes having run well on debut at Geelong. She resumes off a solid trial now for the top yard and should take beating. SUCCAFORYOU (12) made good improvement second up at Geelong when giving a sight up front. She'll take catching from the low gate with a fitness edge. LICENSE TO EXCITE (9) has been solid in two runs back and has claims. FULLY FUNDED (8) can run well on debut.
